This paper deals with the analysis of Twitter users and their characteristics, which falls under the scope of social media analysis. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for predicting offline influence based on Twitter data, which is related to information retrieval and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
